options.markdown:
This Dashboard  displays metrics related to outputs from the collectd based curl plugin which runs a curl request against a supplied URL every 10 seconds.  The following metrics are collected:

**HTTP Response Code** - A 200 response code is considered normal.  4xx/5xx codes  may indicate a problem

**Total Time** - Total time for the curl request/response (includes DNS loopup time).  Any longer times may indicate a problem.

**Response time** - Time measured in seconds for requested payload object to be delivered.

**DNS lookup time** - Time measured in seconds for the client to resolve the DNS hostname.

**Bytes downloaded** -  Total size of response object in  kb.

For more info on the collectd curl plugin and additional metrics available click [here] (https://collectd.org/documentation/manpages/collectd.conf.5.shtml#plugin_curl):

[Markdown Cheatsheet] (https://github.com/adam-p/markdown-here/wiki/Markdown-Cheatsheet)

Link to HTTP Check zappos [homepage] (https://www.zappos.com/)

RED Metrics by Service R - Requests
E - Errors
D - Duration

chart.name: Output drops due to microburst
chart.programText:
A = data('if_errors.rx', rollup='rate').sum().publish(label='A', enable=False)
B = data('if_errors.tx', rollup='rate').sum().publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = (A+B).publish(label='C', enable=False)
D = (C).count().below(0, inclusive=True).publish(label='D', enable=False)
H = data('if_errors.rx', filter=filter('host_kernel_name', 'windows'), rollup='rate').sum().publish(label='H', enable=False)
I = data('if_errors.tx', filter=filter('host_kernel_name', 'windows'), rollup='rate').sum().publish(label='I', enable=False)
J = (H+I).publish(label='J', enable=False)
K = (J).count().below(0, inclusive=True).publish(label='K', enable=False)
L = (J*(D+1)).sum().publish(label='L')
M = (C*(K+1)).sum().publish(label='M')
N = (C+J).sum().publish(label='N')
